data.description:
Nestled in a charming corner lot across from Lexington Park, this timeless 1951 home exudes a welcoming aura with its classic 1 1/2 story design and a rich history of only two owners! With five bedrooms and two and a half baths, this residence is a haven of space and comfort.  The interior of the house has been lovingly maintained and updated, preserving its vintage charm while incorporating modern comforts. The backyard is a floral paradise, meticulously tended to, and filled with a stunning array of flowers along with a beautiful pergola where you can unwind, entertain, or simply revel in the beauty of nature right at your doorstep.
A heated three-stall garage, a rare find that not only accommodates your vehicles but also serves as a versatile space for hobbies, storage, or even as a workshop.

This home is ready for it's newest chapter - YOU!

Freshly refinished wood flooring, new carpet, fresh paint throughout.  Heating elements on both stoops, stairs AND under the gutter covers!
